race in the wilderness; even Israel, when I went to cause him to rest.","year":-606},{"id":"recnVRetIyWe7HWdL","ref":"Jer.31.3","text":"The LORD hath appeared of old unto me, saying, Yea, I have loved thee with an everlasting love: therefore with lovingkindness have I drawn thee.","year":-606},{"id":"reccOFI5tNZSvO8Ij","ref":"Jer.31.4","text":"Again I will build thee, and thou shalt be built, O virgin of Israel: thou shalt again be adorned with thy tabrets, and shalt go forth in the dances of them that make merry.","year":-606},{"id":"recwE5aGaYAGnQ7XQ","ref":"Jer.31.5","text":"Thou shalt yet plant vines upon the mountains of Samaria: the planters shall plant, and shall eat them as common things.","year":-606},{"id":"recFc1Xh9PgupFiYK","ref":"Jer.31.6","text":"For there shall be a day, that the watchmen upon the mount Ephraim shall cry, Arise ye, and let us go up to Zion unto the LORD our God.","year":-606},{"id":"recPe9FKKfGEgNKQS","ref":"Jer.31.7","text":"For thus saith the LORD; Sing with gladness for Jacob, and shout among the chief of the nations: publish ye, praise ye, and say, O LORD, save thy people, the remnant of Israel.","year":-606},{"id":"reccbPO7lE2HSOks2","ref":"Jer.31.8","text":"Behold, I will bring them from the north country, and gather them from the coasts of the earth, and with them the blind and the lame, the woman with child and her that travaileth with child together: a great company shall return thither.","year":-606}]}
